Screenshot of DJII Pronounced like the letter &ldquo;G&rdquo;
DJII was designed by Dana Jessen and Ted Moore during 2021-2022 and coded by Ted Moore in SuperCollider. The software is designed to be used by an improvising solo musician as supporting electronics material.
The modular GUI design allows for intuitive exploration of sound possibilities including flexible matrix-based routing. Software-wide state save and recall enables performer navigation through different preplanned sections of a performance.
